<h2 id=3D"help"><span class=3D"ez-toc-section" id=3D"user-guide"></span>Use=
r Guide<span class=3D"ez-toc-section-end"></span></h2>
<p>This converter and conversion scale will convert the volumetric flow rat=
e (V/t) of a gas or liquid to the equivalent value in different units and d=
isplay a set of related conversions values.</p>
<ol>
<li>Enter the volume flow rate value to be converted in the upper input box=
.</li>
<li>Select the corresponding volumetric and time units from the upper pair =
of selection boxes to define the flow rate measurement unit.</li>
<li>Select the volumetric and time unit for the flow rate unit you are conv=
erting to, from the lower pair of selection boxes.</li>
<li>The converted rate of flow value will display in the lower text box.</l=
i>
</ol>
<h4><span class=3D"ez-toc-section" id=3D"conversion-factors"></span>Convers=
ion Factors<span class=3D"ez-toc-section-end"></span></h4>
<p>The volumetric flow rate (V/t) conversions calculated by this tool are d=
erived from the following SI unit values in cubic metres (m=C2=B3) and seco=
nds (s).</p>
<h6><span class=3D"ez-toc-section" id=3D"volume-v"></span>Volume (V)<span c=
lass=3D"ez-toc-section-end"></span></h6>
<p>The following volumetric units and associated conversion factors in cubi=
c metres (SI unit for volume) are used by this volume flow rate unit conver=
ter:</p>
<ul>
<li>cubic nanometre (cu nm) =E2=80=93 1 x 10<sup>-27</sup> m=C2=B3</li>
<li>cubic micrometre (cu =C2=B5m) =E2=80=93 1 x 10<sup>-18</sup> m=C2=B3</l=
i>
<li>cubic thou (cu thou) =E2=80=93&nbsp;1.6387064 x 10<sup>-14</sup>&nbsp;m=
=C2=B3</li>
<li>cubic millimetre (cu mm) =E2=80=93 1 x 10<sup>-9</sup> m=C2=B3</li>
<li>cubic centimetre (cu cm) =E2=80=93 1 x 10<sup>-6</sup> m=C2=B3</li>
<li>millilitre (mL) =E2=80=93 1 x 10<sup>-6</sup> m=C2=B3</li>
<li>teaspoon (tsp, usa) =E2=80=93 4.92892159375 x 10<sup>-6</sup> m=C2=B3</=
li>
<li>teaspoon (tsp, metric) =E2=80=93 5 x 10<sup>-6</sup> m=C2=B3</li>
<li>tablespoon (Tbsp, usa) =E2=80=93 1.478676478125 x 10<sup>-5</sup> m=C2=
=B3</li>
<li>tablespoon (Tbsp, metric) =E2=80=93 1.5 x 10<sup>-5</sup> m=C2=B3</li>
<li>cubic inch (cu in) =E2=80=93 1.6387064 x 10<sup>-5</sup> m=C2=B3</li>
<li>fluid ounce (fl oz, imperial) =E2=80=93 2.84130625 x 10<sup>-5</sup> m=
=C2=B3</li>
<li>fluid ounce (fl oz, usa) =E2=80=93 2.95735295625 x 10<sup>-5</sup> m=C2=
=B3</li>
<li>cup (usa) =E2=80=93 2.365882365 x 10<sup>-4</sup> m=C2=B3</li>
<li>cup (metric) =E2=80=93 2.5 x 10<sup>-4</sup> m=C2=B3</li>
<li>pint (pt, usa liquid) =E2=80=93 4.73176473 x 10<sup>-4</sup> m=C2=B3</l=
i>
<li>pint (pt, imperial) =E2=80=93 5.6826125 x 10<sup>-4</sup> m=C2=B3</li>
<li>litre (L) =E2=80=93 1 x 10<sup>-3</sup> m=C2=B3</li>
<li>gallon (gal, usa liquid) =E2=80=93 3.785411784 x 10<sup>-3</sup> m=C2=
=B3</li>
<li>gallon (gal, imperial) =E2=80=93 4.54609 x 10<sup>-3</sup> m=C2=B3</li>
<li>cubic foot (cu ft) =E2=80=93 0.028316846592 m=C2=B3</li>
<li>barrel (bbl, oil) =E2=80=93 0.158987294928 m=C2=B3</li>
<li>cubic yard (cu yd) =E2=80=93 0.764554857984 m=C2=B3</li>
<li>cubic metre (cu m) =E2=80=93 1 m=C2=B3</li>
<li>kilolitre (kL) =E2=80=93 1 m=C2=B3</li>
<li>megalitre (ML) =E2=80=93 1000 m=C2=B3</li>
<li>cubic kilometre (cu km) =E2=80=93 1 x 10<sup>+9</sup> m=C2=B3</li>
<li>cubic mile (cu mi) =E2=80=93 4168181825.440579584 m=C2=B3</li>
<li>cubic nautical mile (cu nmi) =E2=80=93 6352182208 m=C2=B3</li>
</ul>
<h6><span class=3D"ez-toc-section" id=3D"time-t"></span>Time (t)<span class=
=3D"ez-toc-section-end"></span></h6>
<p>The following units of time converted into seconds (SI units) are used b=
y this volumetric flow rate conversion tool:</p>
<ul>
<li>nanosecond (ns) =E2=80=93 0.000000001 s</li>
<li>microsecond (=C2=B5s) =E2=80=93 0.000001 s</li>
<li>millisecond (ms, msec) =E2=80=93 0.001 s</li>
<li>second (s, sec) =E2=80=93 1 s</li>
<li>minute (min) =E2=80=93 60 s</li>
<li>hour (h) =E2=80=93 3600 s</li>
